<TITLE> Khaleda says Saifur's death an 'irreparable loss' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 5 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson and former prime minister Khaleda Zia expressed her deep shock Saturday over the death of M Saifur Rahman, veteran BNP leader and former finance minister, calling it "an irreparable loss" for her party and the country. Rahman was pronounced dead at Brahmanbaria Sadar Hospital at around 3pm following a road accident on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway. "The nation has lost a wise politician. It is an irreparable loss that has caused a huge vacuum in the national politics," Khaleda said in a statement. She prayed for peace for the departed soul and extended her sympathy to the bereaved family. She described his eventful life. "He played a vital role in establishing the BNP and later in its organising work as well as being a close confidante of president Ziaur Rahman." "He played a significant role in re-establishing democracy ... He had a vast role, too, in repairing the country's devastated economy and eastablishing it on a strong footing." "We worked together for a long time. He helped me greatly as an honest and skilled colleague in running the government. As a wise economist, he won national and international fame." BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain, former BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan, among others, condoled his death. bdne
